   4:Generated_Source\PSoC4/PWM_ONE_SECOND.c **** *
   5:Generated_Source\PSoC4/PWM_ONE_SECOND.c **** * Description:
   6:Generated_Source\PSoC4/PWM_ONE_SECOND.c **** *  The PWM User Module consist of an 8 or 16-bit counter with two 8 or 16-bit
   7:Generated_Source\PSoC4/PWM_ONE_SECOND.c **** *  comparitors. Each instance of this user module is capable of generating
   8:Generated_Source\PSoC4/PWM_ONE_SECOND.c **** *  two PWM outputs with the same period. The pulse width is selectable between
   9:Generated_Source\PSoC4/PWM_ONE_SECOND.c **** *  1 and 255/65535. The period is selectable between 2 and 255/65536 clocks.
  10:Generated_Source\PSoC4/PWM_ONE_SECOND.c **** *  The compare value output may be configured to be active when the present
  11:Generated_Source\PSoC4/PWM_ONE_SECOND.c **** *  counter is less than or less than/equal to the compare value.
  12:Generated_Source\PSoC4/PWM_ONE_SECOND.c **** *  A terminal count output is also provided. It generates a pulse one clock
  13:Generated_Source\PSoC4/PWM_ONE_SECOND.c **** *  width wide when the counter is equal to zero.
  14:Generated_Source\PSoC4/PWM_ONE_SECOND.c **** *
  15:Generated_Source\PSoC4/PWM_ONE_SECOND.c **** * Note:
  16:Generated_Source\PSoC4/PWM_ONE_SECOND.c **** *
  17:Generated_Source\PSoC4/PWM_ONE_SECOND.c **** *******************************************************************************
